PlantCat.Source: King & Forsyth 2021 The handbook of New Zealand mammals
PlantCat.Notes: This species has not been sighted since 1965, so little is known about it, but its diet is presumed to be similar to M. tuberculata, consisting of arthropods, fruit, nectar, and pollen. We evenly divide Plant between Fruit and Nectar.

PlantCat.Notes: Based on skull morphology, diet may consist of mostly nectar, similar to its close relative Platalina genovensium (which EltonTraits categorizes as 100% nectivorous) and in contrast to other species in the tribe Lonchophyllini (which also consume insects, fruit, and flower parts in addition to nectar).
